<db:para>With QDomNodeList and QDomNamedNodeMap two collection classes are provided: QDomNodeList is a list of nodes, and QDomNamedNodeMap is used to handle unordered sets of nodes (often used for attributes).</db:para>
<db:para>The QDomImplementation class allows the user to query features of the DOM implementation.</db:para>
<db:para>To get started please refer to the QDomDocument documentation. You might also want to take a look at the <db:link xlink:href="qtxml-dombookmarks-example.xml">DOM Bookmarks Example</db:link>, which illustrates how to read and write an XML bookmark file (XBEL) using DOM.</db:para>
